{
  "video_id": "S-3qnZrVy9o",
  "title": "The history of human emotions | Tiffany Watt Smith",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12856.0,
      "end_time": 15530.0,
      "text": "I would like to begin with a little experiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15555.0,
      "end_time": 18646.0,
      "text": "In a moment, I&#39;m going to ask if you would close your eyes"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18670.0,
      "end_time": 20142.0,
      "text": "and see if you can work out"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20166.0,
      "end_time": 23760.0,
      "text": "what emotions you&#39;re feeling right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23100.0,
      "end_time": 25412.0,
      "text": "Now, you&#39;re not going to tell anyone or anything."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25436.0,
      "end_time": 29863.0,
      "text": "The idea is to see how easy or perhaps hard you find it"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29887.0,
      "end_time": 32479.0,
      "text": "to pinpoint exactly what you&#39;re feeling."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32503.0,
      "end_time": 35944.0,
      "text": "And I thought I&#39;d give you 10 seconds to do this."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35968.0,
      "end_time": 37412.0,
      "text": "OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37436.0,
      "end_time": 39123.0,
      "text": "Right, let&#39;s start."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48150.0,
      "end_time": 49527.0,
      "text": "OK, that&#39;s it, time&#39;s up."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 49551.0,
      "end_time": 50775.0,
      "text": "How did it go?"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51113.0,
      "end_time": 53681.0,
      "text": "You were probably feeling a little bit under pressure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53705.0,
      "end_time": 55870.0,
      "text": "maybe suspicious of the person next to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55895.0,
      "end_time": 58618.0,
      "text": "Did they definitely have their eyes closed?"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58642.0,
      "end_time": 61852.0,
      "text": "Perhaps you felt some strange, distant worry"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 61876.0,
      "end_time": 64206.0,
      "text": "about that email you sent this morning"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 64230.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67384.0,
      "text": "or excitement about something you&#39;ve got planned for this evening."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67408.0,
      "end_time": 70553.0,
      "text": "Maybe you felt that exhilaration that comes when we get together"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 70577.0,
      "end_time": 72320.0,
      "text": "in big groups of people like this;"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72344.0,
      "end_time": 74512.0,
      "text": "the Welsh called it \"hwyl,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74536.0,
      "end_time": 76886.0,
      "text": "from the word for boat sails."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 77660.0,
      "end_time": 80314.0,
      "text": "Or maybe you felt all of these things."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 80338.0,
      "end_time": 83762.0,
      "text": "There are some emotions which wash the world in a single color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 83787.0,
      "end_time": 86796.0,
      "text": "like the terror felt as a car skids."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 87344.0,
      "end_time": 89942.0,
      "text": "But more often, our emotions crowd and jostle together"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89966.0,
      "end_time": 92803.0,
      "text": "until it is actually quite hard to tell them apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 93351.0,
      "end_time": 97142.0,
      "text": "Some slide past so quickly you&#39;d hardly even notice them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 97166.0,
      "end_time": 99594.0,
      "text": "like the nostalgia that will make you reach out"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 99618.0,
      "end_time": 102208.0,
      "text": "to grab a familiar brand in the supermarket."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102949.0,
      "end_time": 105351.0,
      "text": "And then there are others that we hurry away from,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 105375.0,
      "end_time": 107265.0,
      "text": "fearing that they&#39;ll burst on us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 107956.0,
      "end_time": 111955.0,
      "text": "like the jealousy that causes you to search a loved one&#39;s pockets."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 112860.0,
      "end_time": 115768.0,
      "text": "And of course, there are some emotions which are so peculiar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 115792.0,
      "end_time": 117867.0,
      "text": "you might not even know what to call them."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 117891.0,
      "end_time": 120770.0,
      "text": "Perhaps sitting there, you had a little tingle of a desire"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 120794.0,
      "end_time": 125112.0,
      "text": "for an emotion one eminent French sociologist called \"ilinx,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 125136.0,
      "end_time": 128662.0,
      "text": "the delirium that comes with minor acts of chaos."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 128686.0,
      "end_time": 132336.0,
      "text": "For example, if you stood up right now and emptied the contents of your bag"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 132360.0,
      "end_time": 133556.0,
      "text": "all over the floor."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 133580.0,
      "end_time": 137507.0,
      "text": "Perhaps you experienced one of those odd, untranslatable emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137531.0,
      "end_time": 140316.0,
      "text": "for which there&#39;s no obvious English equivalent."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 140340.0,
      "end_time": 143625.0,
      "text": "You might have felt the feeling the Dutch called \"gezelligheid,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143649.0,
      "end_time": 147781.0,
      "text": "being cozy and warm inside with friends when it&#39;s cold and damp outside."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 148273.0,
      "end_time": 150589.0,
      "text": "Maybe if you were really lucky,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 150613.0,
      "end_time": 151807.0,
      "text": "you felt this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 152358.0,
      "end_time": 153705.0,
      "text": "\"basorexia,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153729.0,
      "end_time": 155766.0,
      "text": "a sudden urge to kiss someone."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 155790.0,
      "end_time": 157844.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 158799.0,
      "end_time": 160602.0,
      "text": "We live in an age"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 160626.0,
      "end_time": 164810.0,
      "text": "when knowledge of emotions is an extremely important commodity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 165530.0,
      "end_time": 168552.0,
      "text": "where emotions are used to explain many things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 169192.0,
      "end_time": 171109.0,
      "text": "exploited by our politicians,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 171133.0,
      "end_time": 173264.0,
      "text": "manipulated by algorithms."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 173288.0,
      "end_time": 178138.0,
      "text": "Emotional intelligence, which is the skill of being able to recognize and name"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 178162.0,
      "end_time": 180638.0,
      "text": "your own emotions and those of other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 180662.0,
      "end_time": 184849.0,
      "text": "is considered so important, that this is taught in our schools and businesses"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 184873.0,
      "end_time": 187200.0,
      "text": "and encouraged by our health services."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 187962.0,
      "end_time": 189785.0,
      "text": "But despite all of this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 189809.0,
      "end_time": 190988.0,
      "text": "I sometimes wonder"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 191120.0,
      "end_time": 194895.0,
      "text": "if the way we think about emotions is becoming impoverished."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 195491.0,
      "end_time": 199850.0,
      "text": "Sometimes, we&#39;re not even that clear what an emotion even is."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 201509.0,
      "end_time": 203454.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ve probably heard the theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 203479.0,
      "end_time": 206630.0,
      "text": "that our entire emotional lives can be boiled down"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 206870.0,
      "end_time": 209321.0,
      "text": "to a handful of basic emotions."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 209345.0,
      "end_time": 211810.0,
      "text": "This idea is actually about 2,000 years old,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 211834.0,
      "end_time": 212998.0,
      "text": "but in our own time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 213220.0,
      "end_time": 217286.0,
      "text": "some evolutionary psychologists have suggested that these six emotions --"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 217311.0,
      "end_time": 222650.0,
      "text": "happiness, sadness, fear, disgust, anger, surprise --"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 222890.0,
      "end_time": 225628.0,
      "text": "are expressed by everyone across the globe in exactly the same way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 225652.0,
      "end_time": 228334.0,
      "text": "and therefore represent the building blocks"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 228359.0,
      "end_time": 231180.0,
      "text": "of our entire emotional lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 231420.0,
      "end_time": 233209.0,
      "text": "Well, if you look at an emotion like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 233233.0,
      "end_time": 235362.0,
      "text": "then it looks like a simple reflex:"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 235386.0,
      "end_time": 237622.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s triggered by an external predicament,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 237646.0,
      "end_time": 239427.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s hardwired,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 239451.0,
      "end_time": 242490.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s there to protect us from harm."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 242730.0,
      "end_time": 244537.0,
      "text": "So you see a bear, your heart rate quickens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 244561.0,
      "end_time": 248762.0,
      "text": "your pupils dilate, you feel frightened, you run very, very fast."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 249878.0,
      "end_time": 251964.0,
      "text": "The problem with this picture is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 251989.0,
      "end_time": 256870.0,
      "text": "it doesn&#39;t entirely capture what an emotion is."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 256591.0,
      "end_time": 259550.0,
      "text": "Of course, the physiology is extremely important,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 259574.0,
      "end_time": 262725.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s not the only reason why we feel the way we do"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 262749.0,
      "end_time": 264324.0,
      "text": "at any given moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 266102.0,
      "end_time": 269800.0,
      "text": "What if I was to tell you that in the 12th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 269104.0,
      "end_time": 272856.0,
      "text": "some troubadours didn&#39;t see yawning"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 272880.0,
      "end_time": 276630.0,
      "text": "as caused by tiredness or boredom like we do today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 276654.0,
      "end_time": 280800.0,
      "text": "but thought it a symbol of the deepest love?"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 280907.0,
      "end_time": 285145.0,
      "text": "Or that in that same period, brave men -- knights --"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 285170.0,
      "end_time": 288459.0,
      "text": "commonly fainted out of dismay?"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 289474.0,
      "end_time": 290716.0,
      "text": "What if I was to tell you"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 290740.0,
      "end_time": 293503.0,
      "text": "that some early Christians who lived in the desert"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 293527.0,
      "end_time": 297414.0,
      "text": "believed that flying demons who mainly came out at lunchtime"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 297439.0,
      "end_time": 302301.0,
      "text": "could infect them with an emotion they called \"accidie,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 302325.0,
      "end_time": 304919.0,
      "text": "a kind of lethargy that was sometimes so intense"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 304943.0,
      "end_time": 306431.0,
      "text": "it could even kill them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 307234.0,
      "end_time": 311370.0,
      "text": "Or that boredom, as we know and love it today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 311394.0,
      "end_time": 314421.0,
      "text": "was first really only felt by the Victorians,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 314445.0,
      "end_time": 319621.0,
      "text": "in response to new ideas about leisure time and self-improvement?"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 320570.0,
      "end_time": 322700.0,
      "text": "What if we were to think again"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 322940.0,
      "end_time": 324912.0,
      "text": "about those odd, untranslatable words for emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 324936.0,
      "end_time": 329166.0,
      "text": "and wonder whether some cultures might feel an emotion more intensely"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 329190.0,
      "end_time": 332986.0,
      "text": "just because they&#39;ve bothered to name and talk about it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 333100.0,
      "end_time": 335479.0,
      "text": "like the Russian \"toska,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 335503.0,
      "end_time": 338210.0,
      "text": "a feeling of maddening dissatisfaction"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 338234.0,
      "end_time": 340768.0,
      "text": "said to blow in from the great plains."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 343111.0,
      "end_time": 347750.0,
      "text": "The most recent developments in cognitive science show"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 347100.0,
      "end_time": 350491.0,
      "text": "that emotions are not simple reflexes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 350515.0,
      "end_time": 353625.0,
      "text": "but immensely complex, elastic systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 353649.0,
      "end_time": 356797.0,
      "text": "that respond both to the biologies that we&#39;ve inherited"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 356821.0,
      "end_time": 359470.0,
      "text": "and to the cultures that we live in now."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 359494.0,
      "end_time": 361590.0,
      "text": "They are cognitive phenomena."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 361614.0,
      "end_time": 364563.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re shaped not just by our bodies, but by our thoughts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 364587.0,
      "end_time": 367416.0,
      "text": "our concepts, our language."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 367979.0,
      "end_time": 372409.0,
      "text": "The neuroscientist Lisa Feldman Barrett has become very interested"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 372433.0,
      "end_time": 376177.0,
      "text": "in this dynamic relationship between words and emotions."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 376558.0,
      "end_time": 380100.0,
      "text": "She argues that when we learn a new word for an emotion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 380350.0,
      "end_time": 382933.0,
      "text": "new feelings are sure to follow."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 384272.0,
      "end_time": 388252.0,
      "text": "As a historian, I&#39;ve long suspected that as language changes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 388276.0,
      "end_time": 389959.0,
      "text": "our emotions do, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 390527.0,
      "end_time": 394426.0,
      "text": "When we look to the past, it&#39;s easy to see that emotions have changed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 394450.0,
      "end_time": 396373.0,
      "text": "sometimes very dramatically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 396398.0,
      "end_time": 399891.0,
      "text": "in response to new cultural expectations and religious beliefs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 399915.0,
      "end_time": 403410.0,
      "text": "new ideas about gender, ethnicity and age,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 403650.0,
      "end_time": 407336.0,
      "text": "even in response to new political and economic ideologies."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 408106.0,
      "end_time": 411504.0,
      "text": "There is a historicity to emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 411528.0,
      "end_time": 414940.0,
      "text": "that we are only recently starting to understand."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 416228.0,
      "end_time": 420399.0,
      "text": "So I agree absolutely that it does us good to learn new words for emotions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 420423.0,
      "end_time": 422819.0,
      "text": "but I think we need to go further."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 422843.0,
      "end_time": 425517.0,
      "text": "I think to be truly emotionally intelligent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 425541.0,
      "end_time": 429853.0,
      "text": "we need to understand where those words have come from,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 429877.0,
      "end_time": 434550.0,
      "text": "and what ideas about how we ought to live and behave"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 434790.0,
      "end_time": 436251.0,
      "text": "they are smuggling along with them."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 437753.0,
      "end_time": 439558.0,
      "text": "Let me tell you a story."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 439582.0,
      "end_time": 443712.0,
      "text": "It begins in a garret in the late 17th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 443736.0,
      "end_time": 446262.0,
      "text": "in the Swiss university town of Basel."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 446286.0,
      "end_time": 451951.0,
      "text": "Inside, there&#39;s a dedicated student living some 60 miles away from home."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 451975.0,
      "end_time": 453767.0,
      "text": "He stops turning up to his lectures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 453791.0,
      "end_time": 458511.0,
      "text": "and his friends come to visit and they find him dejected and feverish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 458535.0,
      "end_time": 460401.0,
      "text": "having heart palpitations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 460425.0,
      "end_time": 462890.0,
      "text": "strange sores breaking out on his body."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 463338.0,
      "end_time": 464502.0,
      "text": "Doctors are called,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 464526.0,
      "end_time": 467405.0,
      "text": "and they think it&#39;s so serious that prayers are said for him"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 467429.0,
      "end_time": 468585.0,
      "text": "in the local church."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 468609.0,
      "end_time": 471813.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s only when they&#39;re preparing to return this young man home"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 471838.0,
      "end_time": 473300.0,
      "text": "so that he can die,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 473540.0,
      "end_time": 474784.0,
      "text": "that they realize what&#39;s going on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 474809.0,
      "end_time": 477560.0,
      "text": "because once they lift him onto the stretcher,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 477800.0,
      "end_time": 478777.0,
      "text": "his breathing becomes less labored."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 478801.0,
      "end_time": 481596.0,
      "text": "And by the time he&#39;s got to the gates of his hometown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 481620.0,
      "end_time": 483744.0,
      "text": "he&#39;s almost entirely recovered."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 484186.0,
      "end_time": 485599.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s when they realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 485623.0,
      "end_time": 489788.0,
      "text": "that he&#39;s been suffering from a very powerful form of homesickness."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 489812.0,
      "end_time": 492285.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s so powerful, that it might have killed him."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 493347.0,
      "end_time": 496614.0,
      "text": "Well, in 1688, a young doctor, Johannes Hofer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 496639.0,
      "end_time": 498671.0,
      "text": "heard of this case and others like it"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 498695.0,
      "end_time": 501802.0,
      "text": "and christened the illness \"nostalgia.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 502843.0,
      "end_time": 506323.0,
      "text": "The diagnosis quickly caught on in medical circles around Europe."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 506347.0,
      "end_time": 508919.0,
      "text": "The English actually thought they were probably immune"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 508943.0,
      "end_time": 511777.0,
      "text": "because of all the travel they did in the empire and so on."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 511802.0,
      "end_time": 514350.0,
      "text": "But soon there were cases cropping up in Britain, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 514374.0,
      "end_time": 517242.0,
      "text": "The last person to die from nostalgia"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 517265.0,
      "end_time": 521921.0,
      "text": "was an American soldier fighting during the First World War in France."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 523363.00000000006,
      "end_time": 526932.0,
      "text": "How is it possible that you could die from nostalgia"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 526956.0,
      "end_time": 528768.0,
      "text": "less than a hundred years ago?"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 528792.0,
      "end_time": 531864.0,
      "text": "But today, not only does the word mean something different --"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 531888.0,
      "end_time": 535324.0,
      "text": "a sickening for a lost time rather than a lost place --"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 535348.0,
      "end_time": 538646.0,
      "text": "but homesickness itself is seen as less serious,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 538670.0,
      "end_time": 541211.0,
      "text": "sort of downgraded from something you could die from"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 541235.0,
      "end_time": 544484.0,
      "text": "to something you&#39;re mainly worried your kid might be suffering from"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 544508.0,
      "end_time": 545676.0,
      "text": "at a sleepover."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 545700.0,
      "end_time": 549818.0,
      "text": "This change seems to have happened in the early 20th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 549842.0,
      "end_time": 551610.0,
      "text": "But why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 551850.0,
      "end_time": 555317.0,
      "text": "Was it the invention of telephones or the expansion of the railways?"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 555341.0,
      "end_time": 558322.0,
      "text": "Was it perhaps the coming of modernity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 558346.0,
      "end_time": 562750.0,
      "text": "with its celebration of restlessness and travel and progress"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 562990.0,
      "end_time": 564616.0,
      "text": "that made sickening for the familiar"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 564640.0,
      "end_time": 566236.0,
      "text": "seem rather unambitious?"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 567324.0,
      "end_time": 572342.0,
      "text": "You and I inherit that massive transformation in values,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 572366.0,
      "end_time": 575622.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s one reason why we might not feel homesickness today"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 575647.0,
      "end_time": 577663.0,
      "text": "as acutely as we used to."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 579139.0,
      "end_time": 581195.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s important to understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 581219.0,
      "end_time": 584755.0,
      "text": "that these large historical changes influence our emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 584779.0,
      "end_time": 588594.0,
      "text": "partly because they affect how we feel about how we feel."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 588991.0,
      "end_time": 591506.0,
      "text": "Today, we celebrate happiness."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 591988.0,
      "end_time": 595257.0,
      "text": "Happiness is supposed to make us better workers"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 595281.0,
      "end_time": 597448.0,
      "text": "and parents and partners;"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 597472.0,
      "end_time": 599948.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s supposed to make us live longer."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 599972.0,
      "end_time": 601797.0,
      "text": "In the 16th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 601821.0,
      "end_time": 604669.0,
      "text": "sadness was thought to do most of those things."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 604693.0,
      "end_time": 608910.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s even possible to read self-help books from that period"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 608115.0,
      "end_time": 610688.0,
      "text": "which try to encourage sadness in readers"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 610712.0,
      "end_time": 613678.0,
      "text": "by giving them lists of reasons to be disappointed."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 613702.0,
      "end_time": 614744.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 614768.0,
      "end_time": 619150.0,
      "text": "These self-help authors thought you could cultivate sadness as a skill,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 619390.0,
      "end_time": 622197.0,
      "text": "since being expert in it would make you more resilient"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 622221.0,
      "end_time": 625703.0,
      "text": "when something bad did happen to you, as invariably it would."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 626195.0,
      "end_time": 628631.0,
      "text": "I think we could learn from this today."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 628655.0,
      "end_time": 633826.0,
      "text": "Feel sad today, and you might feel impatient, even a little ashamed."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 633850.0,
      "end_time": 637947.0,
      "text": "Feel sad in the 16th century, and you might feel a little bit smug."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 639391.0,
      "end_time": 642661.0,
      "text": "Of course, our emotions don&#39;t just change across time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 642686.0,
      "end_time": 644924.0,
      "text": "they also change from place to place."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 645526.0,
      "end_time": 650104.0,
      "text": "The Baining people of Papua New Guinea speak of \"awumbuk,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 650129.0,
      "end_time": 654307.0,
      "text": "a feeling of lethargy that descends when a houseguest finally leaves."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 654331.0,
      "end_time": 655418.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 655442.0,
      "end_time": 658310.0,
      "text": "Now, you or I might feel relief,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 658550.0,
      "end_time": 660171.0,
      "text": "but in Baining culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 660196.0,
      "end_time": 663273.0,
      "text": "departing guests are thought to shed a sort of heaviness"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 663297.0,
      "end_time": 665510.0,
      "text": "so they can travel more easily,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 665750.0,
      "end_time": 668203.0,
      "text": "and this heaviness infects the air and causes this awumbuk."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 668227.0,
      "end_time": 671480.0,
      "text": "And so what they do is leave a bowl of water out overnight"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 671720.0,
      "end_time": 672248.0,
      "text": "to absorb this air,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 672272.0,
      "end_time": 675648.0,
      "text": "and then very early the next morning, they wake up and have a ceremony"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 675672.0,
      "end_time": 676896.0,
      "text": "and throw the water away."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 676920.0,
      "end_time": 678183.0,
      "text": "Now, here&#39;s a good example"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 678207.0,
      "end_time": 682244.0,
      "text": "of spiritual practices and geographical realities combining"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 682268.0,
      "end_time": 684722.0,
      "text": "to bring a distinct emotion into life"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 684746.0,
      "end_time": 686506.0,
      "text": "and make it disappear again."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 687836.0,
      "end_time": 692469.0,
      "text": "One of my favorite emotions is a Japanese word, \"amae.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 693425.0,
      "end_time": 695757.0,
      "text": "Amae is a very common word in Japan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 695781.0,
      "end_time": 697809.0,
      "text": "but it is actually quite hard to translate."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 697833.0,
      "end_time": 700372.0,
      "text": "It means something like the pleasure that you get"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 700396.0,
      "end_time": 704390.0,
      "text": "when you&#39;re able to temporarily hand over responsibility for your life"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 704414.0,
      "end_time": 705718.0,
      "text": "to someone else."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 705742.0,
      "end_time": 706752.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 706776.0,
      "end_time": 708443.0,
      "text": "Now, anthropologists suggest"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 708467.0,
      "end_time": 712495.0,
      "text": "that one reason why this word might have been named and celebrated"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 712519.0,
      "end_time": 713707.0,
      "text": "in Japan"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 713731.0,
      "end_time": 717665.0,
      "text": "is because of that country&#39;s traditionally collectivist culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 717689.0,
      "end_time": 720755.0,
      "text": "whereas the feeling of dependency"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 720779.0,
      "end_time": 723639.0,
      "text": "may be more fraught amongst English speakers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 723663.0,
      "end_time": 727922.0,
      "text": "who have learned to value self-sufficiency and individualism."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 729152.0,
      "end_time": 731539.0,
      "text": "This might be a little simplistic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 731563.0,
      "end_time": 733317.0,
      "text": "but it is tantalizing."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 733889.0,
      "end_time": 739263.0,
      "text": "What might our emotional languages tell us not just about what we feel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 739287.0,
      "end_time": 742194.0,
      "text": "but about what we value most?"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 744877.0,
      "end_time": 748981.0,
      "text": "Most people who tell us to pay attention to our well-being"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 749500.0,
      "end_time": 752714.0,
      "text": "talk of the importance of naming our emotions."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 752738.0,
      "end_time": 755971.0,
      "text": "But these names aren&#39;t neutral labels."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 755995.0,
      "end_time": 759220.0,
      "text": "They are freighted with our culture&#39;s values and expectations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 759244.0,
      "end_time": 762570.0,
      "text": "and they transmit ideas about who we think we are."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 763650.0,
      "end_time": 767722.0,
      "text": "Learning new and unusual words for emotions will help attune us"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 767746.0,
      "end_time": 771233.0,
      "text": "to the more finely grained aspects of our inner lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 771802.0,
      "end_time": 775508.0,
      "text": "But more than this, I think these words are worth caring about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 775532.0,
      "end_time": 778875.0,
      "text": "because they remind us how powerful the connection is"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 778899.0,
      "end_time": 780391.0,
      "text": "between what we think"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 780415.0,
      "end_time": 782241.0,
      "text": "and how we end up feeling."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 783156.0,
      "end_time": 787170.0,
      "text": "True emotional intelligence requires that we understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 787195.0,
      "end_time": 791999.0,
      "text": "the social, the political, the cultural forces"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 792230.0,
      "end_time": 795556.0,
      "text": "that have shaped what we&#39;ve come to believe about our emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 795580.0,
      "end_time": 801698.0,
      "text": "and understand how happiness or hatred or love or anger"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 801722.0,
      "end_time": 804209.0,
      "text": "might still be changing now."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 804698.0,
      "end_time": 807586.0,
      "text": "Because if we want to measure our emotions"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 807610.0,
      "end_time": 809553.0,
      "text": "and teach them in our schools"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 809577.0,
      "end_time": 813186.0,
      "text": "and listen as our politicians tell us how important they are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 813210.0,
      "end_time": 815410.0,
      "text": "then it is a good idea that we understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 815434.0,
      "end_time": 817390.0,
      "text": "where the assumptions we have about them"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 817414.0,
      "end_time": 818593.0,
      "text": "have come from,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 818618.0,
      "end_time": 821922.0,
      "text": "and whether they still truly speak to us now."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 823478.0,
      "end_time": 825558.0,
      "text": "I want to end with an emotion I often feel"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 825582.0,
      "end_time": 827566.0,
      "text": "when I&#39;m working as a historian."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 827590.0,
      "end_time": 830510.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a French word, \"dépaysement.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 830495.0,
      "end_time": 835304.0,
      "text": "It evokes the giddy disorientation that you feel in an unfamiliar place."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 835328.0,
      "end_time": 837424.0,
      "text": "One of my favorite parts of being a historian"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 837448.0,
      "end_time": 839932.0,
      "text": "is when something I&#39;ve completely taken for granted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 839956.0,
      "end_time": 842527.0,
      "text": "some very familiar part of my life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 842551.0,
      "end_time": 844635.0,
      "text": "is suddenly made strange again."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 845262.0,
      "end_time": 848790.0,
      "text": "Dépaysement is unsettling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
